 Asia is that a "river city" is one where proximity between a river and a city exists across time and space, natural and social dimensions. Recognition of these deep connections can help to better contextualize policy solutions aimed at rivers and their ecologies, including human life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCities and townszAsia. 4aAsia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aAsian history. 4aCity and town planning: architectural aspects. 4aContemporary Society. 4aDevelopment Studies. 4aHistory. 4aReligion and Theology. 4aScience and Technology. 4aUrban communities. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aRiver cities, Southeast Asia, development.1 aCoelho, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDamayanti, Vera D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDick, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFollmann, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuahk, Youngah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanungo, Pralay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiao, Kuei-Hsien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadawangi, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPadawangi, Rita, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerkasa, Adrian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerkasa, Adrian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPrescott, Michaela F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vo